Full Description: 3G Warehouse opened its doors in 2009 as one of Long Island's only woman-owned warehousing operations in New York. Lauren Nichols comes from an industrious line of warehouse owners. Her grandfather, Leonard, began his transportation and warehousing company in the late 1940's with one truck and a dream. His ambitious and driven son, Lawrence, succeeded him in the 1980's. Successful management of a business venture not only confirms commitment to the work but to the well-being of the enterprise. After years of cultivating the business and teaching Lauren the ropes, her father gave his blessing and encouraged Lauren to open her own warehousing company in 2009. 3G Warehouse is the perfect name as Lauren is a third generation warehouse owner. 3G Warehouse views itself as an extension of their clients' companies. Making exceptional customer service their priority, 3G walks clients through their processes to find the most expedient yet cost-effective way to move their companies forward. Today 3G Warehouse works conjointly with their in-house transportation company. Their combined resources enable 3G customers to bring in, store, ship and deliver goods seamlessly. With ever increasing transportation costs cutting into customer profit margins, 3G Warehouse is able to help their customers secure competitive transportation rates without forgoing exceptional service. 3G Warehouse has storage facilities in New York, New Jersey and Nevada. Give us a call to learn how they can offer you exceptional service with the personalized touch of a family-owned business.
